## 5  Five-Tier Resolution Chain

For each vulnerability attempt tiers in order, stopping at the first success:

|Tier|Name                           |Confidence|Description                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                   |
|----|-------------------------------|----------|----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|
|T1  |KB Exact Match                 |0.99      |Look up `groupId:artifactId` + current version + CVE IDs in local KB cache. If found, use pre-validated safe version directly.                                                                                                                                                                                                                |
|T2  |NexusIQ Remediation API        |0.90      |Call NexusIQ REST API for remediation recommendation. Only accept if recommended version covers **ALL** CVE IDs for that artifact. Fall through if `NO_FIX` or partial coverage.                                                                                                                                                              |
|T3  |Maven Central Safe Version Scan|0.75      |**KEY tier for “no fix available” cases.** Query Maven Central for all versions > current. Sort ascending (semver-aware, not lexicographic). For each candidate call NexusIQ component risk API. Return the **lowest** version whose max severity is not CRITICAL or HIGH. This catches fixes NexusIQ hasn’t mapped to a remediation path yet.|
|T4  |Exclusion Strategy             |0.70      |Used when artifact is transitive and no safe version exists anywhere. If 1–2 parents pull it in: add per-parent `<exclusion>` tags. If 3+ parents: add `<dependencyManagement>` override (cleaner, global). Always add a safe direct `<dependency>` after excluding.                                                                          |
|T5  |ACS Suppress + Audit Trail     |0.40      |Last resort only. Log CVE, artifact, reason, timestamp to suppression audit file. Add to `suppressed[]` list, never to `fixed[]`.                                                                                                                                                                                                             |

